<element xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xmlns:zenta="http://magwas.rulez.org/zenta"
         xsi:type="zenta:BasicObject"
         name="KISS"
         id="a554b350-a076-44e8-96bb-083ca197c1fd"
         ancestor="behaviour">
   <documentation>Keep it simple, stupid.
* Extract the complex logic to other method.
* Avoid the use of else. (see https://softwareengineering.stackexchange.com/questions/206816/clarification-of-avoid-if-else-advice ) for clarifications.
* Return early
* Throw exception
* One method should do one thing and one thing well
* Use short methods
* Use classes with only a few methods
* Keep number of fields low.</documentation>
</element>
